Short feedback after using iPhone 14 pro for couple of weeks,

Camera: Overall Great, excellent detailing, portrait photos are class apart, less smoothening and polishing of skin (everyone won‚Äôt like the pic without polishing). Night photos are also good.

Battery Life: I bought this phone expecting to have a good battery life. But in overall, average to below average battery life even after turning off always-on display.

Interface: Overall smooth, I haven‚Äôt faced any bugs. User interface is as usual fluidic and without lags

Display and brightness; Great. Display is very crisp and bright for all the conditions (outdoor).

Dynamic Island: Just consider this as a gimmick. Don‚Äôt consider this feature as a reason to switch to this phone. It makes easy to switch between apps during driving. Especially if you want to see the music player when navigation (map) is on.

Speakers: Great

Bottomline: Don‚Äôt buy this phone for the current Indian market price. It is not offering anything new from previous phones other than small improvements. Feedback from a long term iPhone user.

I've been an ipad user for last 4 Years. With 64gb storage you'll easily run out of storage - particularly with the newer ios updates and ios apps (compared with android) . End result is that your hands are tied - having great processing power without space for using it and i had to offload a lot of apps. Knowingly apple charges heavily for next higher memory upgrade.
Also do account for price of apple pencil (1st gen ~10k) which adds to total cost and mind you newer ipads don't support 1st gen pencil meaning it's use ends once tab is expired.
Display is another major concern if your planning to watch movies or games. Lacks 120hz, can't be compared with amoled and worst of all bleeding issues and large visible white spots (~2yr of usage). Sound quality is way low when compared with 4 speaker akg support in samsung.
Now I'm super happy with tab s7 plus with new android 12L (tab optimised). Coming from an apple system - it's Far far worth its price..
